THE WIZARD'S LAIR - Written by David Williams(Devlin) 2010-2014

You found my secret message! I guess you got curious, huh?
Beating the game with the Warmaster Ending will unlock piles of cool lore and stuff.

There's no DRM - You could probably turn on Debug mode if you're good, but it's only a bunch of stuff to help me test the game.
Some words about the version names! They have kind-of boring stories but I felt that I should document why they were named as such in case people were curious!

v200 Our Hero - It was named as such because it was the first version you could in fact actually buy! (The version actually jumped up at this point, I don't think there's v201-203 out in public circulation)

v204 Viridian - I named this version Viridian because I had just played the word in a game of scrabble and it was stuck in my head for a while!

v205 Hardcore - I actually hugely ramped up the difficulty in this build of TWL, because people were waltzing through it at an alarming rate!

v206 Ellipsis - Yep. You guessed it. James Bond. Mostly because I implemented Dalton and Daniel who are important characters.

v207 Legendary Edition - Because it is the game of legend ;)

v208 Mythical Edition - I chose this name because it's a step up from legendary.

Well, that's all! I really hope you enjoyed the game and that you'll consider buying my future titles!
